Name:         African Wild Dog
Scientific:   Lycaon pictus
Class:        Mammalia
Habitat:      Savanna
Diet:         Carnivore
Lifespan:     11 years
Weight:       30 kg
Status:       Endangered
Fact:         80% hunting success rate; votes on hunts by sneezing democratically

Name:         Arctic Fox
Scientific:   Vulpes lagopus
Class:        Mammalia
Habitat:      Arctic tundra
Diet:         Omnivore
Lifespan:     3 years
Weight:       3.5 kg
Status:       Least Concern
Fact:         Fur changes color seasonally; survives -70 degrees Celsius

Name:         African Elephant
Scientific:   Loxodonta africana
Class:        Mammalia
Habitat:      Savanna
Diet:         Herbivore
Lifespan:     70 years
Weight:       6000 kg
Status:       Vulnerable
Fact:         Largest land animal; strongest sense of smell; mourns the dead

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Nash Equilibrium
Branch:       Game Theory
Formula:      No player benefits from unilateral strategy change
Applications: Economics, AI, political science
Discoverer:   John Nash (1950)

Theorem/Law:  Binomial Theorem
Branch:       Algebra
Formula:      (a+b)^n = sum of C(n,k) a^k b^(n-k)
Applications: Probability, statistics, polynomial algebra
Discoverer:   Newton/Pascal (1665)

Theorem/Law:  Four Color Theorem
Branch:       Topology
Formula:      Any planar map needs at most 4 colors
Applications: Cartography, graph coloring
Discoverer:   Appel and Haken (1976)

